    intro_text: 'The velvet jacket occupies a singular position in British menswear — a piece with roots in Victorian and Edwardian evening dress that has survived into the twenty-first century as one of the few genuinely festive garments available to men. It asks for confidence and a degree of deliberate occasion-dressing; a velvet jacket worn half-heartedly, as though the wearer is uncertain of his choice, will always appear more costume than considered. Worn with conviction and the right supporting pieces, it is among the most striking and memorable things a man can put on for an evening event, a dinner party or the festive season.',
