    dos_and_donts: 'Do invest in the correct collar size — a shirt that is even half a size too tight at the collar will be uncomfortable and will never sit correctly\nDo have shirts altered for sleeve length if necessary — this is a simple and inexpensive tailoring alteration\nDo press the collar carefully — a soft or crumpled collar undermines the entire shirt\'s appearance and by extension the suit\'s\nDon\'t tuck a shirt loosely into suit trousers — the shirt should be tucked firmly and remain so throughout the day\nAvoid wearing a formal dress shirt with the tail untucked — it is designed to be worn tucked and the extra length of a dress shirt makes it look disproportionate if left out\nNever wear a heavily starched shirt with a soft-shouldered suit — the rigidity of the shirt and the ease of the suit will look as though they come from different wardrobes',
