    dos_and_donts: 'Do ensure all three pieces are from the same cloth — mixing components from different suits defeats the purpose of the three-piece\nDo consider proportions carefully: the jacket, waistcoat and trouser must all fit correctly for the ensemble to work\nDo press the waistcoat as carefully as the jacket — it is the most visible piece when the jacket is removed\nDon\'t over-accessorise a three-piece suit — the waistcoat is already a statement and additional layers of jewellery, pins and printed scarves add noise rather than character\nAvoid wearing a three-piece suit with overly casual footwear — it requires shoes that match its authority\nNever fasten the bottom button of the suit jacket — the convention applies to a two-button jacket whether worn with or without a waistcoat',
